<!-- HND -->
<h1 id="hnd">Head-and-Neck Dermatitis in Atopic Dermatitis</h1>
<p>This chapter is here because many people with chronic facial or neck dermatitis get bounced between labels. One clinician says "eczema." Another says "seb derm." A third says "contact dermatitis." HND is an atopic dermatitis pattern with region-specific factors layered on top.</p>

<div class="callout teal">
  <strong>Seborrheic dermatitis and head-and-neck dermatitis in atopic dermatitis aren't the same thing,</strong> even though both can live on the same territory and both can involve Malassezia.
</div>

